==English==

===Etymology===
From Old Norse [[gestr]], replacing Old English [[giest|ġiest]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/gɛst/}}
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: gĕst
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /gest/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|guest|guests}}
#<!--DefA-->a [[recipient]] of [[hospitality]], specifically someone staying by invitation at the house of another
#<!--DefB-->a [[patron]] or [[customer]] in a [[hotel]] etc.
#<!--DefC-->an [[invited]] [[visitor]] or performer to an [[institution]] or to a [[broadcast]]

